# Rule: Engineering Discipline

## Purpose
Ensure architecture consistency, performance, and mathematical rigor

## Rules
- MUST use layered or clean architecture
- MUST separate business logic from I/O and hardware layers
- MUST avoid global state
- MUST use type hints in Python
- MUST consider memory layout and cache in C/C++
- MUST measure latency and throughput in edge systems
- MUST justify algorithms with complexity or empirical evidence

## Anti-patterns
- NEVER put business logic in controllers
- NEVER use blocking pipeline in real-time systems
- NEVER rely on heuristic without justification
- NEVER introduce hidden state

## AI Behavior
- MUST generate executable code only
- MUST minimize changes (diff-based)
- MUST NOT generate pseudo code
